\left(\frac12\right)^2 + \left(\frac12\right)^4 + \left(\frac12\right)^6 + ... = \left(\frac12\right)^2\left(\frac{1}{1-\left(\frac12\right)^2}\right) = \frac{1}{3}
S=\frac1{2^2}+\frac1{2^4}+\frac1{2^6}+\cdots
\implies 4S=1+\frac1{2^2}+\frac1{2^4}+\frac1{2^6}+\cdots
4S-S=1
=\frac{\frac1{2^2}}{1-\frac1{2^2}}
